link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: If p is prime, a(p) = 31 + p.
mathematica: a[n_] := DivisorSum[n, EulerPhi[n/#] * DivisorSigma[0, #]^5 &]; Array[a, 20] (* _Amiram Eldar_, May 10 2021 *)
program: (PARI) a(n) = sumdiv(n, i, sumdiv(n, j, sumdiv(n, k, sumdiv(n, l, sumdiv(n, m, gcd([i, j, k, l, m]))))));
(PARI) a(n) = sumdiv(n, i, sumdiv(n, j, sumdiv(n, k, sumdiv(n, l, sumdiv(n, m, n/lcm([i, j, k, l, m]))))));
